ğŸ“ Directory Creation Using Sequence

mkdir day{1..90}
Creates directories day1 to day90 in seconds.

ğŸ“ Dynamic Directory Creation Script
Example script: createDirectories.sh

#!/bin/bash
for i in $(seq $2 $3); do
  mkdir "$1$i"
done



./createDirectories.sh day 1 90
ğŸ” Loop Example

for i in {1..10}; do echo $i; done
ğŸ”’ User Management
Create users:


sudo useradd user1
sudo useradd user2
Check all users:

cut -d: -f1 /etc/passwd
ğŸ’¾ Backup Script Basics
Create a backup:


tar -czvf backup_$(date +%F).tar.gz /path/to/your/work
Backup script example:



#!/bin/bash
tar -czvf backup_$(date +%F).tar.gz /home/yourname/projects
â±ï¸ Cron & Crontab
Open crontab:


crontab -e
Run backup daily at 1 AM:


0 1 * * * /path/to/backup.sh


These commands are vital in automating DevOps tasks, managing users securely, and maintaining reliable backup processes.